===Etymology 1===
{{PIE root|en|bʰruHg}}
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|brouken||to use, enjoy}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|brūcan||to enjoy, brook, use, possess, partake of, spend}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*brūkaną||to enjoy, use}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*bʰruHg-||to enjoy}}. Cognate with {{etyl|sco|-}} {{m|sco|brook}}, {{m|sco|brouk||to use, enjoy}}, {{etyl|fy|-}} {{m|fy|brûke||to use}}, {{etyl|nl|-}} {{m|nl|bruiken||to use}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{m|de|brauchen||to need, require, use}}, {{etyl|la|-}} {{m|la|fruor||enjoy}}. Related to {{l|en|fruit}}.

